And this data set contains all kinds of crazy information on everything from characters

00:07:24.140 --> 00:07:28.779
and films to physical characteristics of home planets.

00:07:28.779 --> 00:07:32.899
And so we'll be digging into that a little bit today.

00:07:32.899 --> 00:07:37.339
So I'm going to start inside of RStudio just to help us get our bearings a little bit.

00:07:37.339 --> 00:07:41.380
I'm using a flavor of RStudio called RStudio Server Pro.

00:07:41.380 --> 00:07:47.059
So you can see I've accessed RStudio through a web browser, which might be new to some

00:07:47.059 --> 00:07:48.059
of you.

00:07:48.059 --> 00:07:50.619
But otherwise, the ID is exactly the same.

00:07:50.619 --> 00:07:56.059
And everything that I'm going to show you today, you'll be able to do inside of RStudio

00:07:56.059 --> 00:08:02.380
Open Source Server, RStudio Server Pro, or just on RStudio Desktop, which is most likely

00:08:02.380 --> 00:08:04.420
what you guys are using.

00:08:04.420 --> 00:08:05.540
All right.

00:08:05.540 --> 00:08:11.880
So as Nathan mentioned, one of the most common forms of communication and communicating the

00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:16.220
results of analysis is just with a static piece of content.

00:08:16.540 --> 00:08:21.619
And one of the, again, most popular pieces of static content are just plots and visualizations.

00:08:21.619 --> 00:08:24.380
So that's what we're going to start off with today.

